FX  - The research described in this paper was conducted as part of the project "Utilizing Remote Sensing for Evaluating Climate Change Im-pacts on Agriculture in Afghanistan: A Case Study of Bamyan Province" funded by the International Development Research Center (IDRC) Canada through the Afghan Research Initiative (ARI) based out of University of Central Asia (UCA) . We thank Dr. Bohdan Krawchenko at UCA for his efforts in securing and supporting this project. This initiative involves an integrated evaluation of farmers' crop selections through ground surveys and remote sensing techniques to formulate recommendations for adapting the agricultural sector to projected climate changes.
