KW  - Climate disaster
KW  - Crop insurance
KW  - Farmers' income
KW  - AGRICULTURAL INSURANCE
KW  - ECONOMIC-IMPACT
KW  - YIELD
AB  - Climate disasters inflict significant harm on natural ecosystems, while agricultural output losses escalate alongside the aggravation of global warming. Crop insurance is one of the most important risk management tools for agricultural producers to reduce the losses caused by climate disasters through risk distribution and disaster mitigation technologies. Utilizing panel data from 30 Chinese provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions (2007-2019), this paper empirically analyzed the moderating role of crop insurance in alleviating the impacts of climate disasters. The findings demonstrate that climate disasters adversely affect farmers' income; however, crop insurance can mitigate this negative impact. Although crop insurance has experienced rapid growth, its development is uneven, disproportionately concentrated in economically underdeveloped regions. Consequently, China should further strengthen the policy support for sustainable development and equitable dissemination of crop insurance.
